The paper discusses mixed-initiative interaction in interactive applications, which is a topic closely related to human-computer interaction (HCI). Therefore, cs.HCI is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of partial evaluation as a programming model, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (AI) and programming languages (PL). The paper also mentions voice-based interaction technologies, which are often studied in the sub-category of natural language processing (NLP) or computational linguistics (CL). Finally, the paper discusses dialog management systems, which can be considered a sub-topic of software engineering (SD).
